| Scenario            | Why Actions is Required    |
| ------------------- | -------------------------- |
| Hover menus         | Menu appears only on hover |
| Drag and Drop       | Element must be dragged    |
| Right Click         | Context menu interaction   |
| Double Click        | Special UI behaviour       |
| Keyboard shortcuts  | CTRL+C, CTRL+A             |
| Click and hold      | Sliders or resize bars     |
| Drawing or gestures | Canvas interaction         |


| Method          | Use Case             |
| --------------- | -------------------- |
| moveToElement() | Hover over element   |
| click()         | Click                |
| doubleClick()   | Double click         |
| contextClick()  | Right click          |
| dragAndDrop()   | Drag element         |
| clickAndHold()  | Hold mouse           |
| release()       | Release held mouse   |
| sendKeys()      | Keyboard typing      |
| keyDown()       | Press keyboard key   |
| keyUp()         | Release keyboard key |

Mouse hover:
actions
.moveToElement(menu)
.click(subMenu)
.build()
.perform();

Syntax:
WebElement menu = driver.findElement(By.xpath("//a[text()='Menu']"));
Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
actions.moveToElement(menu).perform();

Double click:
WebElement element = driver.findElement(By.id("doubleClickBtn"));
Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
actions.doubleClick(element).perform();

Right click:
WebElement element = driver.findElement(By.id("contextMenu"));
Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
actions.contextClick(element).perform();

Drag & Drop:
WebElement source = driver.findElement(By.id("drag"));
WebElement target = driver.findElement(By.id("drop"));
Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
actions.dragAndDrop(source, target).perform();

Keyboard Combination:
Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
actions.keyDown(Keys.CONTROL)
       .sendKeys("a")
       .keyUp(Keys.CONTROL)
       .perform();

actions.click(goingTextbox)      // Moves the cursor to the element
       .sendKeys("del")
       .sendKeys(Keys.TAB)       // moves the focus to the next UI element
       .sendKeys(Keys.ENTER)     // used to select a suggestion from a dropdown
       .build()
       .perform();

| Method          | Syntax                                          | Purpose                      | Example Scenario        |
| --------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | --------------------------   | ----------------------- |
| moveToElement() | actions.moveToElement(element).perform();       | Hover over element           | Open dropdown menu      |
| click()         | actions.click(element).perform();               | Click using mouse simulation | When normal click fails |
| doubleClick()   | actions.doubleClick(element).perform();         | Double click action          | Open editor             |
| contextClick()  | actions.contextClick(element).perform();        | Right click                  | Context menu            |
| clickAndHold()  | actions.clickAndHold(element).perform();        | Hold mouse button            | Drag start              |
| release()       | actions.release().perform();                    | Release mouse                | Drop element            |
| dragAndDrop()   | actions.dragAndDrop(src, dest).perform();       | Drag element                 | Drag box                |
| dragAndDropBy() | actions.dragAndDropBy(element, x, y).perform(); | Move element by coordinates  | Slider movement         |
| sendKeys()      | actions.sendKeys(Keys.ENTER).perform();         | Keyboard action              | Submit form             |
| keyDown()       | actions.keyDown(Keys.CONTROL)                   | Hold key                     | CTRL selection          |
| keyUp()         | actions.keyUp(Keys.CONTROL)                     | Release key                  | End keyboard combo      |
| build()         | actions.build().perform();                      | Execute multiple actions     | Complex workflow        |


